1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,047
[Azuelo] <i>Our mission is to capture</i>
<i>and arrest Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

2
00:00:06,131 --> 00:00:08,550
<i>We are not going to the island</i>
<i>to kill anyone.</i>

3
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:11,845
[Datu] <i>Son, we need to defend ourselves!</i>

4
00:00:11,928 --> 00:00:14,889
<i>They are killing our people!</i>

5
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:15,765
Father, don't!

6
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:16,933
- [gunshots]
- [shouts]

7
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:19,394
Datu Rahman spotted. Pursuing.

8
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:23,606
- [shouting]
- [gunshots]

9
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:25,108
[Marcus] <i>The mission is compromised.</i>

10
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:26,568
I repeat, the mission is compromised.

11
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:28,153
We need to help Marcus.

12
00:00:28,236 --> 00:00:30,530
It will take hours to get there.

13
00:00:30,613 --> 00:00:32,699
[Lara] <i>So you're going to let</i>
<i>Marcus and his troop die?</i>

14
00:00:32,782 --> 00:00:34,451
[Azuelo] <i>Occupational hazard.</i>

15
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:35,618
<i>Go back to your station.</i>

16
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,871
<i>You can help them from there.</i>

17
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:39,998
[gunshot]

18
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,084
[flesh squelches]

19
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:44,335
[exclaims]

20
00:00:44,919 --> 00:00:45,920
[gunshot]

21
00:00:46,004 --> 00:00:47,505
[tense music]

22
00:00:47,589 --> 00:00:48,840
[shouts]

23
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,679
Before it's too late,
please tell my family,

24
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:56,014
I love them very much,
and I will always be with them.

25
00:00:56,097 --> 00:00:57,724
We will not give up!

26
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,142
We are going back to Manila!

27
00:00:59,225 --> 00:01:00,685
You are coming home to your family!

28
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:01,895
- God is great!
- [Marcus gasps]

29
00:01:03,104 --> 00:01:06,983
We are living in peace
and you attacked us.

30
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,651
[Marcus] We're only here for Datu Rahman.

31
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:12,739
[grunting and groaning]

32
00:01:12,822 --> 00:01:16,367
[grunting]

33
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:18,661
[music concludes]

34
00:01:19,746 --> 00:01:22,332
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,721
[shouts]

36
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:38,223
Jalil!

37
00:01:38,306 --> 00:01:40,308
[tense music]

38
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:43,853
[loud explosion]

39
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:45,313
- [bodies thud]
- [grunts]

40
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:55,115
[static feedback]

41
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,539
- [exclaims]
- [ear-ringing sound]

42
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:05,166
[grunts]

43
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:08,962
- Aah!
- [groans]

44
00:02:09,045 --> 00:02:12,715
[morose music playing]

45
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:14,467
[gasps]

46
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:25,854
[morose music continues]

47
00:02:35,613 --> 00:02:39,325
[grunts]

48
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:42,996
[groaning]

49
00:02:47,292 --> 00:02:48,418
[Datu] Jalil!

50
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,503
[groaning]

51
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,964
[somber music]

52
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:05,518
- [heavy breathing]
- [music concludes]

53
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:07,395
This wasn't supposed to happen.

54
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:09,105
[heavy breathing]

55
00:03:09,188 --> 00:03:14,652
[tense music playing]

56
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,118
Why are you doing this?

57
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,038
You…

58
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:27,790
Datu Rahman Abubakar…

59
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,000
[tense music]

60
00:03:29,083 --> 00:03:30,585
…are under arrest…

61
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:35,798
for violating Republic Act 10591

62
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,760
[inhales]
of the Comprehensive Firearms Act.

63
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:43,556
[tense music continues]

64
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:48,019
[voice cracks] Base to Alpha One.

65
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:52,148
Status! Base to Alpha One, status!

66
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,816
[Marcus] <i>Target apprehended.</i>

67
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,193
[Marcus sighs]

68
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,736
[music fades out]

69
00:03:56,819 --> 00:03:59,239
Good. [sniffles] Good.

70
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:00,907
Proceed to the extraction point.

71
00:04:01,407 --> 00:04:03,368
[morose music playing]

72
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:15,004
[crying]

73
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:22,095
[sniffles, sobs]

74
00:04:24,305 --> 00:04:28,810
[morose music continues]

75
00:04:46,536 --> 00:04:47,954
Why are there only four of you?

76
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:49,872
Where's Harold?!

77
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,917
[grim music playing]

78
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,465
Sir, we have to move now.

79
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:01,217
We are in a dangerous position here.

80
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:03,177
[Marcus] We can't leave him here.

81
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,929
[Lara] Agent Reyes, no.

82
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,764
Get to the extraction point right now!

83
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:08,016
[Felix] Sir, we have to go.

84
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:09,976
Rustia!

85
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:12,895
Rustia!

86
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:15,732
- [people screaming]
- [rapid gunfire]

87
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:17,108
- [gunshots]
- [grunts]

88
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:19,319
Marcus, I need you to get your team

89
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:21,195
to the extraction point right now!

90
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:23,740
- [rapid gunfire]
- [Marcus] Let's go, let's go!

91
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:27,702
- Move! Move!
- [gunshots]

92
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:29,746
[somber music playing]

93
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,374
[headphones thuds]

94
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:34,625
[sniffles]

95
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:37,837
[sighs deeply]

96
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,922
[sniffles]

97
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,633
[sighs deeply]

98
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:43,926
[sniffles]

99
00:05:45,553 --> 00:05:48,848
[crying]

100
00:05:48,931 --> 00:05:52,935
[somber music continues]

101
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:58,524
[Felix] Congratulations, sir.

102
00:05:59,734 --> 00:06:01,152
Mission accomplished! [pats]

103
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,283
[Felix grunts]

104
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:08,451
Argh!

105
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,328
I stopped you, you bastard.

106
00:06:10,411 --> 00:06:11,621
You didn't listen to me!

107
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:13,873
You kept shooting them!
A lot of civilians died!

108
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:16,584
[Felix] Civilians?!
Didn't you see they were armed?!

109
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:20,004
If we didn't shoot them first,
we'd be dead by now!

110
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,214
What?!

111
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:25,009
[somber music playing]

112
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:35,353
[music intensifies]

113
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:48,282
Who gave the order?

114
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,201
Huh? Which order?

115
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,662
To neutralize the whole village!

116
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:54,080
Who gave the order, Lara?

117
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:55,998
Marcus, no one gave such an order.

118
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:57,959
I was monitoring the operations
the whole time.

119
00:06:58,042 --> 00:06:58,960
- I didn't hear that order.
- Someone ordered it, Lara!

120
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:00,545
- No one gave such an order.
- There was!

121
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,922
- Someone gave that order, Lara!
- Agent Reyes, calm down!

122
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,590
- Lara, I heard it!
- Calm down, Agent Reyes!

123
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,759
Tell me who gave the order.

124
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:08,302
Say it!

125
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,179
[tense music]

126
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:13,558
Lara, a lot of innocent people died, okay?

127
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:17,145
Even Harold! Harold got left behind!

128
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,982
[Marcus breathing heavily]

129
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:25,486
I didn't even get to bring his body home
for his family to have a burial!

130
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:26,404
- [object thuds]
- [Marcus breathing heavily]

131
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:27,822
[sighs]

132
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:29,907
I'm sorry, Agent Reyes. I'm sorry.

133
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:31,617
[Marcus breathing heavily]

134
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:32,660
I'm sorry, Marcus.

135
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:34,996
[Marcus breathing heavily]

136
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:38,124
Do you think it's possible
someone hijacked our comms?

137
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:46,799
[unsettling music playing]

138
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:48,342
[secretary] Sir, wait.

139
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:50,470
You have to stay here.
You can't go inside.

140
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:55,308
[unsettling music continues]

141
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:58,853
[Marcus breathing heavily]

142
00:07:58,936 --> 00:08:00,229
Agent Reyes.

143
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,233
The man of the hour.

144
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:06,277
Congratulations!

145
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:08,946
Sir, I need to talk to you.

146
00:08:11,115 --> 00:08:12,408
You look tense.

147
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,329
Why don't we have a drink,
so you can relax?

148
00:08:18,247 --> 00:08:19,499
With all due respect, sir,

149
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,584
this is not a time to celebrate.

150
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,253
Someone hijacked our comms.

151
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:26,797
Someone fired a gun
that put everything into chaos!

152
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:29,258
[sinister music]

153
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:31,135
The mission is successful!

154
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,387
Loosen up!

155
00:08:35,973 --> 00:08:36,974
Loosen up?

156
00:08:39,894 --> 00:08:41,312
Loosen up, sir?

157
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:46,359
A lot of innocent people died.

158
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:48,402
Harold got left behind, and he's dead!

159
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:50,696
- Don't you care?!
- Agent Reyes!

160
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,950
In our line of work…

161
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:56,285
death is inevitable!

162
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,706
Harold's death…

163
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:01,874
It's tragic.

164
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:06,420
But that's the reason
why your mission was successful.

165
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:08,714
So just…

166
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,841
take the win!

167
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,678
This is not a win, sir!

168
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:16,764
- [heavy breathing]
- [unsettling music continues]

169
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:23,020
Get out.

170
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:28,192
Get out.

171
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:33,948
[unsettling music continues]

172
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:46,002
[birds chirping]

173
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:49,714
[villagers wailing]

174
00:09:49,797 --> 00:09:52,800
[somber music playing]

175
00:09:52,883 --> 00:09:54,510
[woman shouting]

176
00:09:54,594 --> 00:10:00,224
[wailing]

177
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:01,767
[woman shouts]

178
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:04,228
[wailing, screaming]

179
00:10:04,312 --> 00:10:05,813
[woman shouts]

180
00:10:05,896 --> 00:10:11,902
[villagers wailing]

181
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:21,746
[somber music continues]

182
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,965
[women screaming]

183
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:34,884
[woman shouting]

184
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:39,305
[women wailing]

185
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:46,187
[villagers wailing]

186
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:52,193
[somber music continues]

187
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:56,781
[woman wailing, screaming]

188
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,168
He's alive.

189
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:12,171
If possible, bring him
to the hospital immediately.

190
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:13,422
Be careful.

191
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:18,260
- [wailing, screaming]
- [somber music continues]

192
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:29,480
[Imam speaking in Arabic]

193
00:11:29,563 --> 00:11:32,441
[somber music]

194
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:54,422
[Imam speaking in Arabic]

195
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:03,097
[somber music continues]

196
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:04,640
What's this?

197
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:05,724
What's that?

198
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:10,646
[music intensifies]

199
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:18,696
[somber music continues]

200
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:27,913
[Jamilah crying]

201
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,583
Kah, Amah needs you.

202
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:35,754
Wake up, Kah… [crying]

203
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:38,090
[Jamilah crying]

204
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,259
Wake up…

205
00:12:40,342 --> 00:12:44,180
[Jamilah crying]

206
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:46,557
[Jamilah crying]

207
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,977
[music fades out]

208
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,564
[Jamilah crying]

209
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:55,566
[somber music]

210
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,613
Son… Are you okay?

211
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,867
They said our mission was successful.

212
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:09,872
That's not what I feel.

213
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:12,416
[somber music]

214
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,542
[inhales]

215
00:13:13,626 --> 00:13:16,253
A lot of innocent people died.

216
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,298
Harold…

217
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,800
Harold died, too!

218
00:13:21,884 --> 00:13:23,219
He got left behind!

219
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:28,140
[Marcus breathing heavily]

220
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,226
I came into this job…

221
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:33,187
to protect people.

222
00:13:35,564 --> 00:13:36,857
[Marcus inhales]

223
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,067
I didn't do that.

224
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:41,987
Son, it's not your fault.

225
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:45,866
It could've been you who died
instead of Harold!

226
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:47,201
[Theresa inhales]

227
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:48,494
And I'm sure

228
00:13:48,577 --> 00:13:51,872
Harold wouldn't like it
if you blamed yourself.

229
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:57,419
I know you want to help everyone,

230
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:59,964
but sometimes, there are just things
that are out of our hands.

231
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:01,799
A lot of people died.

232
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,300
Us doctors…

233
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,844
We lose people, too.

234
00:14:06,387 --> 00:14:08,764
[voice quivers] It's sad, but…

235
00:14:08,847 --> 00:14:12,685
We can't stop helping people, son.

236
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:15,563
[somber music playing]

237
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:18,857
- [Theresa crying]
- [sighs]

238
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,150
The best way to…

239
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,903
to honor Harold's life is…

240
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:23,988
[gasps]

241
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:27,199
…to just keep going.

242
00:14:27,783 --> 00:14:30,077
You have to continue your job for Harold.

243
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,954
Live for Harold.

244
00:14:32,037 --> 00:14:34,582
Like what you do for your sibling.

245
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:38,961
[Marcus exhales deeply]

246
00:14:41,463 --> 00:14:44,133
Something wrong happened
with that mission.

247
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:45,217
[gasps]

248
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:48,137
[somber music continues]

249
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:51,932
And my mind won't rest
until I learn the truth.

250
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:54,894
- [gasps]
- [somber music continues]

251
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:10,242
[unsettling music playing]

252
00:15:36,143 --> 00:15:37,269
[grunting, groaning]

253
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:39,104
[grunts, groans, shouts]

254
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:43,567
- [both grunting]
- [knife swishes]

255
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:44,777
- [shouts]
- [knife swishes]

256
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:47,404
[Felix shouts]

257
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:52,034
[breathing rapidly]

258
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:56,872
[inhaling sharply]

259
00:15:56,956 --> 00:16:00,000
[chuckling]

260
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:02,503
[laughing]

261
00:16:02,586 --> 00:16:05,339
[music swells]

262
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:10,386
[music fades, grows weary]

263
00:16:11,178 --> 00:16:12,096
Kah.

264
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:13,681
[Jamilah crying]

265
00:16:13,764 --> 00:16:15,891
Kah, get well soon.

266
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:18,477
[Jamilah crying]

267
00:16:19,561 --> 00:16:22,231
[sobbing] Kah, I will follow Amah.

268
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:24,900
[Jamilah crying]

269
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,695
I can't accept it if I don't do anything…

270
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:29,947
[sobbing] …to save him.

271
00:16:32,574 --> 00:16:33,826
Get well soon, Kah.

272
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:35,494
[Jamilah crying]

273
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:37,246
[Jamilah sniffles]

274
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:43,460
[Jamilah crying]

275
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,424
[Jamilah crying]

276
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,010
[Jamilah sniffles]

277
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:53,512
[Jamilah crying]

278
00:16:53,595 --> 00:16:55,597
Babu… [sobbing]

279
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,766
Babu, take care of my Kakah.

280
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:00,394
Don't worry.

281
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:02,646
I'll be here.

282
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:06,025
Promise? [sobbing]

283
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:07,401
Yes.

284
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:08,777
[sobbing]

285
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,155
I'll get going.

286
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,657
[sobbing]

287
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:18,871
[music intensifies]

288
00:17:18,954 --> 00:17:19,872
[pensive music playing]

289
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:21,874
[female reporter] <i>We're here</i>
<i>right now at the headquarters</i>

290
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:24,001
of the Special Investigations Division

291
00:17:24,084 --> 00:17:25,919
for the presscon on the arrest

292
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:29,048
of the allegedly notorious criminal
and high value target,

293
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,883
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

294
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:33,969
He was arrested by the Task Force Alpha
for the transgression

295
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:36,972
of the Republic Act No. 10591,

296
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:40,851
or Comprehensive Firearms
and Ammunition Regulation Act.

297
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:45,314
Abubakar is said to be responsible
for the smuggling of illegal weapons

298
00:17:45,397 --> 00:17:47,149
in many parts of Mindanao.

299
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:50,486
As of now, the death toll
is yet to be confirmed.

300
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,529
[people clamoring]

301
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:55,240
[woman 1] Criminal! Criminal!

302
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:56,450
Terrorist!

303
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,993
[woman 2] Demon!

304
00:17:58,077 --> 00:17:59,620
[crowd shouting]

305
00:17:59,703 --> 00:18:02,164
- [indistinct shouting]
- [woman 1] Criminal! Criminal!

306
00:18:02,664 --> 00:18:03,957
[woman 2] He deserves jail time!

307
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:07,336
- On March 14,
- [indistinct shouting]

308
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:12,883
the SID and the NLEA's
crime fighting group,

309
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,218
Task Force Alpha,

310
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:18,472
apprehended Datu Rahman Abubakar.

311
00:18:20,557 --> 00:18:24,436
The Task Force laid down
their lives for this mission.

312
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:26,772
Three of them were injured.

313
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:28,190
[somber music]

314
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:30,943
They were Agent Oliver La Peña,

315
00:18:32,152 --> 00:18:34,780
SPO3 Patrick Marquez,

316
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:38,951
and SPO2 Russel Contreras.

317
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:40,911
Unfortunately,

318
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,915
Agent Harold Rustia died.

319
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:48,460
- [man in crowd] Oh, how unfortunate.
- [overlapping chatter]

320
00:18:50,295 --> 00:18:51,255
[grunts] Argh!

321
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:56,051
[fire crackling in distance]

322
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:06,895
[Azuelo] His sacrifices and the entire
task force's were not in vain.

323
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,397
Rest assured…

324
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:13,277
…we will do our best,
together with the police force,

325
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:18,031
to cease the proliferation
of illegal weapons,

326
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:20,576
not only in areas under Datu Rahman,

327
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:22,327
but throughout the country.

328
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,621
- [applause]
- [woman] That's right.

329
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:26,206
[indistinct shouting]

330
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:29,168
- [man] You're an animal!
- [woman] You should be in prison!

331
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:31,086
[indistinct shouting]

332
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,630
[Azuelo] Justice prevails

333
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:37,801
and will continue to be
enforced against crime.

334
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,136
- [woman 1] Demon!
- [woman 2] Terrorist!

335
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:41,555
[indistinct shouting]

336
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:44,683
- [indistinct shouting]
- [woman] Terrorist!

337
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:47,102
[indistinct shouting]

338
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:49,605
[indistinct shouting]

339
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:51,648
[indistinct shouting]

340
00:19:52,316 --> 00:19:54,401
[indistinct shouting]

341
00:19:54,484 --> 00:19:55,986
[indistinct shouting]

342
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:57,779
[indistinct shouting]

343
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,114
[indistinct shouting]

344
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:02,326
[indistinct shouting]

345
00:20:02,409 --> 00:20:04,411
[indistinct shouting]

346
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:06,288
[indistinct shouting]

347
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:07,915
[indistinct shouting]

348
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:11,293
[tense music]

349
00:20:31,396 --> 00:20:35,859
[tense music continues]

350
00:20:45,202 --> 00:20:47,746
Where do you get the weapons
you have on your island?

351
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:49,998
The accusations against me aren't true.

352
00:20:50,082 --> 00:20:51,375
You are the criminal here!

353
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,419
All the footage was wiped out.

354
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:57,005
Who's sabotaging us and why?

355
00:20:57,089 --> 00:21:01,134
[reporter] <i>A team leader who allegedly</i>
<i>massacred an entire community…</i>

356
00:21:01,218 --> 00:21:02,052
- [grunts]
- [loud thud]

357
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:04,513
[woman] Free Datu Rahman!

358
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:06,556
[woman] You'll all be in jail!

359
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,976
[woman] Murderers!

360
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:11,645
[Azuelo] The agency's name
is being tarnished because of you!

361
00:21:11,728 --> 00:21:12,562
[Marcus] <i>Damn it.</i>

362
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,274
The riot was planned.

363
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:17,901
[Marcus] <i>I heard gunshots.</i>

364
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:20,362
That Datu Rahman is pretty tough, no?

365
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:23,699
[Lara] <i>You see what those people</i>
<i>from the island can do for him.</i>

366
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:26,201
- <i>They'll sacrifice their lives for him.</i>
- [sobbing]

367
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,411
<i>Don't let him get to your head.</i>

368
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:30,372
[music intensifies, concludes]
